<br>
Ok, I won't get into how <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> feel the game should have been designed to begin with, but instead I will point out a number of key problems with our class. The first and most glaring problem has to do with perception. With the exception of my guild and my roommate, I don't think that anyone that I have played with really knows what it is that I bring to a group, and even then they don't usually group with Wizards unless its me. This is because in truth they know what it is that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> bring to the group. I'll explain.<br>
<br>
EVERY class that can cast a spell can nuke; and before you start saying that Wizard's nukes are faster, do more damage, or use less mana, I'm not done yet. As a Wizard when you join a group as far as anyone is concerned (even your guild and RL friends who know you real well) the only two things you bring to the group are nukes and teleports. So ask yourself If you are in a group with a warrior, and enchanter, a cleric, and a druid (you are the cleric) are you really going to be looking for a wizard when you can have a mage who can summon items for the casters, and who comes with their own tank that won't need healing. Or perhaps a rogue or other melee type. Wizards are at the bottom of the list (right behind Shadow Knights another favorite class of mine).<br>
<br>
Other players see us as being a very redundant class created specifically for raiding and soloing. Though we all know this to be false, there's really no reason they should not think as they do. If you were to take away a druid's or a shaman's or a necro's nukes you would still have a very good class for any situation. Take away a mage's nukes, and you still have a great summoner. Take away a clerics nukes and you have... a cleric. However, a Wizard <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> her/his nukes, take ours away and you have a taxi, and now that our blasts aren't getting any bigger (from 51 - 60) no one sees what we are doing for the group unless we get a crit.<br>
<br>
Ok, yes, I can solo, and yes, I am needed on raids; but who wants to spend their EQ life soloing and waiting for raids? 3.5 of the casting classes can heal, most can buff (or summon items that act as buffs) and all casting classes (even rangers!) have nukes and in many casses they are equivilent to ours in terms of damage. Since damage is all anyone else really cares about, there really isn't a point it compairing mana or casting time. Sure when someone sees me chain casting Draught of Fire on some mobe that has just ripped a whole in my robe they are extremly impressed, but not so much so that they want me in a group. Why? Because the same thing that makes us who we are (at least at 51+) is the same thing that makes is a liability <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> hard fast nukes!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Sure, I know that many of us know how not to get into trouble (without our Epic or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> uber</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> gear) but the perception is out there.<br>
<br>
I personally don't know what at this point could be done to fix it, but until it is I will only play my Wizard when my roommate needs a teleport (and since he's dating a druid I'm sure that won't be too often).<br>
