 <br>
I will very rarely twitch in a group and its only if someone is dying and the cleric is oom I will twitch enough for a heal then I suggest that the puller stop pulling and the cleric sit on their ass to regain mana like everyone else. There are way more useful things I can be doing with my mana and if the group is too slow I'll go solo. It's not my fault if people can't manage agro, their mana or the speed of the pulls. Being a twitch bitch is just too boring.<br>
<br>
Now on a raid if I can't land spells or lifetap the crap out of a mob then well then twitching gives me something to do but I will not do this in experience groups there is just not reason for it. <br>
<br>
The thing I object to the most is the close mindedness of many people and of their refusal to accept that there might be other things, like causing several K in damage during a long fights, that we can do a lot better and much more efficiently than throwing away more than half our mana while giving it to someone else.<br>
